hello I'm kosif A Cloud support engineer
here at the AWS office in Sydney today
I'm going to show you how to request a
Kota increase if you encounter the
resource limit exceeded error in Amazon
sag maker let's get
started first I'll reproduce this error
log to the AWS Management console and
then choose Amazon
sagemaker choose
Studio select your user profile then
choose Open
studio choose jump start choose your
desired model provider and model I'll
use stability AI stable diffusion xcl
1.0 choose deploy
subscribe if you are not already
subscribed then choose
deploy choose your instance type I will
choose the instance type as shown and
then choose
deploy note that you receive an error as
shown the account level service limit
error this error usually occurs when you
exceed the account level service quotas
that are specified for your sagemaker
resources to to resolve this error let's
open the Service cotas
console make sure that you are logged in
with a user or role that does have
access to modify service cotas make sure
that the region is same as your Sage
maker for me it's North
Virginia in the navigation pane choose
AWS services in the search bar enter
Amazon sag maker and then choose Amazon
Sage maker choose view quotas select the
quota that you want to increase for my
case I'm choosing instance type for
endpoint usage choose request quota
increase enter the desired value for my
case I'm choosing four choose
request this sends your request to AWS
support based on your use case and
current usage your request is either
approved denied or partially approved
and now you know how to request a quota
increase if you encounter the resource
limit exceeded error in Sage
maker thanks for watching and happy
cloud computing from all of us here at
AWS
